Most unusual experience: we were approached by a loon who was very anxious about the Van Dorn bottle he dived under the boat and went down to follow the secchi disk.
Cloudy with a bright sky.  The temperature is very warm at 80 degrees.
Temp 85 F- lots of boats and waves/wake from boats- etc.)
partly cloudy.  Honor to have with today- Vernon Buckheit Myers- Doctorate in Limnology- who works with the
Had to use two different dates because of weather.
The temperature is 11 degrees C at 10 feet.  Measuring now depends on the weather- sun and wind.
Beautiful day- then a storm hit.
Blue sky (first in a week) cumulus clouds.
Weather is very cold now- this will be our last grab for the season in 94.
Saw four small mouth bass at 4' depth.  Lake level: very high
Still- clear-great day.  Merganser family babies on female's back!
Water dark.  Windy- difficult to hold boat.  Next year may sample with algae net and s-r counting.  Chamber for phytoplankton.
Baby ducks- mergansers.  Water rushing through outlet- erosion on some shores- sort of undercutting.  Is this due to wake of large boats   Large rocks are being put in.
Soaring eagles and two immature eagles.
Sea gulls (herring)- no wind- very clear- we need more live.
Beautiful day-turnover complete-a little murky yet.
Windy and cold.  Three loons are back.  West basin not turned over yet.
The water is low. Had trouble getting through to Madison.
loons. Eagles in nest - no young.
West basin is stratified and turnover recent.  It appears a bit murky.
Water too low--coud not go through channel
